# Env / secrets
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
*.env

# Private keys / certs (defense in depth — should never land in git)
*.pem
*.key
*.crt
*.p12
*.pfx
id_rsa
id_ed25519

# Runtime cache & data files (regenerated automatically).
# Reports for the /audit/ and /link-report/ pages — generated by workflows
# and committed via `git add -f` in those workflows so the pages render.
_data/link_cache.json
_data/audit_report.json
_data/link_report.json
_infographic.jpg
# NB: _data/feed_health.json and _data/feed_cache.json are tracked on
# purpose — they hold per-run state (consecutive feed failures, ETag,
# Last-Modified) that has to survive between CI fresh checkouts to be
# useful. Conditional fetch alone saves ~100 MB/day of bandwidth.

# Client-side search index (built in CI by generate_search_index.py).
# NB: this file IS tracked even though it's regenerated — main.js fetches
# it directly, so removing it from the deployed tree would break /search/.
# The file used to be listed here, which gave the false impression it was
# untracked. It is committed; the workflow regenerates and re-commits it.
#
# NB: _videos/*.roundup and *.done markers MUST stay tracked — they enforce
# idempotency between CI runs (fresh checkout would otherwise re-publish
# videos that are already uploaded to YouTube).

# OS / editor
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
